        <Summary>Speech Recognition Engine </Summary>
        <Description>Julius is a high-performance, two-pass large vocabulary continuous speech recognition (LVCSR) engine.It supports N-gram based dictation, DFA grammar based parsing, and one-pass isolated word recognition. Phone context dependencies are supported up to triphone. It can perform a multi-model decoding, a recognition using several LMs and AMs simultaneously with a single processor, and also supports "hot plugging" of arbitrary modules at run time.</Description>
